00:39:35,141 --> 00:39:35,883
Speaker 0: Yeah, mine did too.

616
00:39:35,923 --> 00:39:40,820
Speaker 0: It just, I've had it so long, 10 plus years, that rice cooker anyway.

617
00:39:41,640 --> 00:39:52,340
Speaker 0: But yeah, every device that you have that plugs into the wall is going to be taking some, you know, hopefully like a light, a lamp is going to take zero power when you have it off, right?

618
00:39:52,760 --> 00:39:54,751
Speaker 1: Well, that should accept some smart lamp bullshit.

619
00:39:56,580 --> 00:39:57,061
Speaker 1: Here's the problem.

620
00:39:57,142 --> 00:40:03,380
Speaker 1: Smart lamps draw power to run themselves or LEDs require ballasts and things.

621
00:40:03,500 --> 00:40:09,500
Speaker 1: Like they have to be converted to DC power or voltage up, like fluorescence need voltage up regulation.

622
00:40:09,881 --> 00:40:11,285
Speaker 1: All sorts of nonsense has to happen.

623
00:40:11,706 --> 00:40:16,080
Speaker 1: Anytime you're converting from AC to DC, you have to have a transformer.

624
00:40:16,701 --> 00:40:23,600
Speaker 1: And usually that transformer is between the outlets and your device and will just constantly be leeching power as long as it's plugged in.

